	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001131_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>10 Soho Square</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">11<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir </p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Arrowsmith</persName>
<lb/>sends you a spare 
<lb/>map per bearer. 
<lb/>I am better this 
<lb/>morning and 
<lb/>will I hope be 
<lb/>able to come 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001131_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>tomorrow according 
<lb/>to your kind 
<lb/>invitation. I have 
<lb/>a crude mass of 
<lb/>words of various 
<lb/>African dialects 
<lb/>&amp; one pretty full 
<lb/>vocabulary of 
<lb/>Sichuana the 
<lb/>language of the 
<lb/><term type="tribe">Bechuanas</term> but 
<lb/>have not time 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001131_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>to put it in form 
<lb/>for printing. I 
<lb/>have an analysis 
<lb/>of African languages 
<lb/>too but the same 
<lb/>want of time is 
<lb/>a serious obstacle 
<lb/>to doing anything 
<lb/>with it. <persName>Admiral 
<lb/>Trotter</persName> is in 
<lb/><placeName>Leamington</placeName>
<lb/><placeName>Warwick</placeName>
<lb/>Can you forward 
<lb/>a few of my 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001131_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>books to <choice><sic>to</sic><corr>no text</corr></choice> our 
<lb/>friend <persName>Maclear</persName>
<lb/>free of expense 
<lb/>to him - ? </p>
<lb/><p>Hoping to be 
<lb/>with you tomorrow<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am sincerely </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">yours </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
